.TH "bcm63xx_select_phy_mode" 9 "bcm63xx_select_phy_mode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bcm63xx_select_phy_mode \- Select between USB device and host mode.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" bcm63xx_select_phy_mode
.BI "(struct bcm63xx_udc *udc "  ","
.BI "bool is_device "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "udc" 12
Reference to the device controller.
.IP "is_device" 12
true for device, false for host.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This should probably be reworked to use the drivers/usb/otg
infrastructure.

By default, the AFE/pullups are disabled in device mode, until
\fBbcm63xx_select_pullup\fP is called.
